      "content": "so i was going through my grandfathers old trunk and found this heavy silver signet ring and a silk tapestry that has this weird crest on it... it looks like a sun rising over a mountain but the mountain is cracked in half? i've never seen this crest in any history book and honestly the craftsmanship is way too good for just some random family trinket. it feels like there's a specific meaning to it that i'm missing. can you help me figure out what this symbol might represent?",
